channel.title: Few Song Suggestions
channel.description:
Well, the last thread I posted here was a complete failure because a lot of people thought it was a complete shit song by a complete shit band, so I'm going to give this another attempt until I see that people agree:
Death: Voice of The Soul: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qd4q0Xx-u1Y Painkiller: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=quPliK3eAy4&feature=related A Moment of Clarity: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2uP0PtBurno&feature=related
Pearl Jam: Jeremy - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MS91knuzoOA Nothingman - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CgSR4ltkDCg&feature=related
So tell me what people think of at least these two bands.

item.title: Few Song Suggestions
item.dc:creator: @Ix_Soulcist_xI Soulcist
item.description:
@Ix_Soulcist_xI wrote:

[quote=“Speljohan, post:6, topic:413527”][quote author=Ix Soulcist xI link=topic=515026.msg3740919#msg3740919 date=1315341361]
Thanks a lot, I have heard about them not too long ago from the other song suggestions I posted and I liked them a lot, it made me want to explore music a lot more than I use to and it led me to find some others, and nice song additions to the song collection I’ve added up over the months after I turned from Rap.

Death - I want to learn more about their music and nice songs, I’ll be looking at the songs here in a moment because their an interesting band, so feel free to give me more suggestions from them.

How about feedback for Pearl Jam, what do you think of them?
[/quote]Death haven’t made a single bad album, that’s how brilliant they are.[/quote]
Awesome! Will be listening to all their songs then.
